//Facebook Sales Ad Setup//////////////////////////

To increase sales for your client’s e-commerce website using Facebook Ads 
(actually through Meta Ads Manager), use this structure:

1. Set Up Essentials First

Before running ads, make sure these are ready:

✅ Business website is working well
✅ Product pages have price, images, and “Buy Now” button
✅ Install Meta Pixel on website
✅ Connect Pixel with Ads Manager
✅ Set conversion event like:

View Content
Add to Cart
Initiate Checkout
Purchase

This helps Facebook find buyers.

2. Choose Correct Campaign Objective

In Ads Manager click Create Campaign and choose:

🎯 Sales → Best for getting purchases.

Other useful objectives:

Traffic → send visitors only
Leads → collect customer info
Engagement → likes/comments
Awareness → brand promotion

For e-commerce, choose Sales.

3. Create Campaign

Example:

Campaign Name:
Summer Dress Sales - Bangladesh

Settings:

Turn ON Advantage+ Shopping Campaign if available.
Or use manual sales campaign.
4. Create Ad Set

Here you select audience.

Conversion Location:

Choose Website

Pixel:

Select your Meta Pixel

Conversion Event:

Choose Purchase

Budget:

Example:

Daily Budget: $5–$20/day
or
Lifetime Budget
Audience:

Example if selling fashion:

Location: Bangladesh
Age: 18–40
Gender: Female
Interest:

Online shopping
Fashion
Daraz
Clothing brands

You can also create:

✅ Custom Audience:

Website visitors
Add to cart but no purchase

✅ Lookalike Audience:
Facebook finds similar buyers.

5. Placement

Use Advantage+ Placements (Automatic)

Ads may show on:

Facebook Feed
Instagram Feed
Stories
Reels
Messenger
6. Create Ad Creative

Use attractive:

📷 Product image
or
🎥 Short product video

Ad text example:

Summer Collection is Live 🌸
Buy now and get 20% OFF today!
Fast delivery across Bangladesh 🇧🇩

Headline:
Shop Now

CTA Button: Shop Now

Website URL → Product or category page.

7. Retargeting Ads (Very Important)

Run separate ads for:

People who:

visited website
added to cart
viewed product

Example text:

You forgot something in your cart 🛒
Complete your order now!

Retargeting usually gives more sales.

8. Monitor Results

Check these metrics:

CPA = Cost per purchase
CTR = Click Through Rate
ROAS = Return on Ad Spend
CPC = Cost per click

If ad not performing:

change creative
change audience
test another product
Best Strategy for E-commerce

Run 3 campaigns:

Cold Audience → New people
Retargeting → Visitors/Add to cart
Lookalike → Similar buyers

This is the most common winning strategy.

